{
  "text": "To determine whether OsDr1 and OsDrAp1 interact with each other, we first used the yeast two-hybrid system [CITATION_1] . The coding regions of OsDr1 and OsDrAp1 were inserted into the vectors pAD-Gal4 and pBDGal4 (Stratagene, San Diego, CA) to generate pAD::OsDr1 and pBD::OsDrAp1 constructs, respectively ( Figure 2A ). Yeast cotransformed with pAD::OsDr1 and pBD::OsDrAp1 could grow on Ϫ Trp, Ϫ Leu, and Ϫ His selection media (Figure 2B ). Neither pAD::OsDr1 nor pBD::OsDrAp1 alone could support yeast growth on the triple selection media. To exclude the possibility that there was a mutation in yeast supporting growth on the triple selection media, we performed ␤ -galactosidase assays. The results showed that only the yeast line containing both pAD::OsDr1 and pBD::OsDrAp1 constructs had ␤ -galactosidase activity ( Figure 2C ); yeast (A) OsDr1 was compared with Dr1 from wheat (wDr1), Arabidopsis (aDr1; [CITATION_2] , soybean (sDr1), yeast (yDr1; Kim et al., 1997), human (hDr1; [CITATION_3] , and Drosophila (dDr1; [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "41355367",
